Use this README file to introduce your application and point to useful places in the API for learning more.
Run "rake doc:app" to generate API documentation for your models, controllers, helpers, and libraries.

To create a new instance on Heroku, use the following steps

create an empty database - either clone your repo into a new place, or delete your development.sqlite3
$ rm app/db/migrate/*
$ rails generate hobo:migration
$ rails generate vestal_versions:migration
$ rake db:migrate

$ heroku create  #will return a name, say blue-sky-1234
$ heroku rename --app blue-sky-1234 xx-kanban
$ git push git@heroku.com:xx-kanban.git
$ heroku db:push --app xx-kanban
$ heroku addons:add sendgrid:starter --app xx-kanban

you'll also need to edit 'host' and possibly 'protocol' in production.rb

it should now be possible to create first admin user on heroku instance, then invite users, create projects etc
